  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Down Syndrome is silent population in Pakistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In our Society, no one is aware about Down Syndrome &amp; its causes so that we do not treat children &amp; Persons as they should be. Actually Human cells normally contain 23 pairs of chromosomes. Down syndrome is caused by trisomy 21 - the person has three copies of chromosome 21, instead of the usual two copies, in all cells. Abnormality changes the habits of child, which can be treated through rehabilitation, we need due care for this child for bringing in mainstream life with community awareness.</narrative>
  </description>
